1
00:03:27,734 --> 00:03:28,723
Guard one check.

2
00:03:29,435 --> 00:03:31,426
This is a standard exercise
for the military.

3
00:03:31,738 --> 00:03:34,206
lt's main purpose is to test
the integrity of our system.

4
00:03:34,874 --> 00:03:35,738
Sharon

5
00:03:36,242 --> 00:03:38,472
Operation bug chase commencing
in thirty seconds.

6
00:03:39,312 --> 00:03:40,609
This is an exercise.

7
00:03:40,813 --> 00:03:43,247
l repeat. This is an exercise.

8
00:03:46,052 --> 00:03:47,485
Beetle Alpha, you have a go.

9
00:03:48,321 --> 00:03:49,413
Beetle check.

10
00:03:51,224 --> 00:03:53,283
Beetle Alpha represents
the planes of an imaginary enemy.

11
00:03:53,426 --> 00:03:56,293
They will try to avoid
our radar by flying low.

12
00:03:56,763 --> 00:04:00,426
lf they lock on to
our target with their aiming system,

13
00:04:00,566 --> 00:04:01,658
we lose.

14
00:04:01,801 --> 00:04:02,699
Anything on screen?

15
00:04:02,869 --> 00:04:05,064
We don't have anything,
Sir, they are below one thousand.

16
00:04:13,346 --> 00:04:20,843
Receiving Awac's data, Beetle identified
Designated BD001-002, 2 minute's ETA.

17
00:04:21,587 --> 00:04:24,283
Target on screen,
request firing AlM-120.

18
00:04:25,491 --> 00:04:27,618
Request denied!
Visual identification required.

19
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,590
Affirmative.

20
00:04:35,168 --> 00:04:36,658
Defense radar swipe 1 second.

21
00:04:36,869 --> 00:04:37,767
Yes sir!

22
00:04:43,710 --> 00:04:45,041
Beetle jumping up to one thousand.

23
00:04:45,178 --> 00:04:46,338
They are starting bomb run.

24
00:04:46,546 --> 00:04:47,444
Start ECM.

25
00:04:58,491 --> 00:05:01,051
Two targets locked.
Request firing two AA missiles.

26
00:05:01,194 --> 00:05:03,162
A-4 logged on. Fire! Fire!

27
00:05:05,565 --> 00:05:06,759
Beetle, you are dead!

28
00:05:06,899 --> 00:05:07,957
Guard returning to base.

29
00:05:10,603 --> 00:05:11,695
Well done everybody.

30
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,933
Deactivate all missiles defense system,

31
00:05:16,209 --> 00:05:17,005
Return to normal.

32
00:05:17,143 --> 00:05:19,270
Sir, our system is clean!

33
00:05:19,412 --> 00:05:20,401
Thank you, Colonel!

34
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:24,006
So you mean the Singapore government
is prepared for war?

35
00:05:24,183 --> 00:05:26,174
Traditional warfare, yes.

36
00:05:26,386 --> 00:05:28,149
But another kind of warfare
has developed.

37
00:05:28,454 --> 00:05:30,081
So we have to upgrade our defenses.

38
00:05:30,623 --> 00:05:31,988
Another kind of warfare?

39
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:36,486
Computer warfare, lt is happening
everyday via the lnternet.

40
00:05:36,629 --> 00:05:38,620
Nobody has ever
declared a full-scale war.

41
00:05:38,765 --> 00:05:40,824
But casualties are already very high.

42
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:44,558
We believe if any country
wants to raise a full-scale war,

43
00:05:44,704 --> 00:05:47,172
the first shot won't be
bullets or missiles.

44
00:05:47,306 --> 00:05:48,705
lt will be computer bombs.

45
00:05:50,009 --> 00:05:53,911
Colonel Ng has just been placed in
charge of our lnformation Warfare Unit.

46
00:05:54,514 --> 00:05:57,005
Why 'information', not just 'computers'?

47
00:05:57,650 --> 00:05:59,811
lt is less scary for everyone sir.

48
00:05:59,952 --> 00:06:03,012
You see,
today any laptop computer now can do

49
00:06:03,156 --> 00:06:04,282
a lot more damage than an atomic bomb.

50
00:06:04,424 --> 00:06:06,392
We just hate to remind people.

51
00:06:17,904 --> 00:06:20,031
The ultimate weapon of tomorrow.

52
00:06:20,173 --> 00:06:21,140
This is the sleeper?

53
00:06:21,274 --> 00:06:24,573
l already place this innocent
little sucker into the system l serviced.

54
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:28,040
When they check the system for viruses,
nothing.

55
00:06:28,848 --> 00:06:31,612
But when we use the Caller Program
to wake this little sucker up,

56
00:06:31,784 --> 00:06:34,116
Bingo! The service is ours.

57
00:06:34,787 --> 00:06:36,846
First National Bank at your service, sir.

58
00:06:37,990 --> 00:06:38,820
Did you test it?

59
00:06:38,991 --> 00:06:41,755
What do you mean did l test it?
You gave me a half-finished program!

60
00:06:41,894 --> 00:06:43,555
You told me you'd give me a finished one.

61
00:06:43,696 --> 00:06:44,924
l can't.

62
00:06:45,064 --> 00:06:46,429
The company found out.

63
00:06:46,899 --> 00:06:48,799
Their CEO just called me yesterday,
said...

64
00:06:48,935 --> 00:06:50,698
... someone had stolen
their sleeper design

65
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:52,030
and their caller program.

66
00:06:52,738 --> 00:06:54,399
They'll probably report it to ClA.

67
00:06:54,607 --> 00:06:57,838
But you are the ClA!
You are the head of their security.

68
00:06:58,678 --> 00:07:01,044
l know! That's why
they're reporting to me.

69
00:07:02,181 --> 00:07:05,480
Anyway they'll here in Singapore
in 3 minutes on this plane.

70
00:07:05,751 --> 00:07:07,514
So what am l supposed to do? Stop it now?

71
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,620
No, not that we got this far.

72
00:07:10,790 --> 00:07:12,451
Can you finish
the caller program yourself?

73
00:07:13,526 --> 00:07:15,619
No! l need some time.

74
00:07:15,761 --> 00:07:18,821
l'll need at least a month
on this one, big boy.

75
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:21,897
l'll buy you some time.

76
00:07:22,034 --> 00:07:23,695
Oh? How do you plan on doing that? Huh?

77
00:07:28,374 --> 00:07:29,534
Yes?

78
00:07:31,711 --> 00:07:32,575
Shoot it down!

79
00:08:47,954 --> 00:08:48,978
Trying to escape?

80
00:08:58,464 --> 00:08:59,192
Shit!

81
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:03,533
Have you ever been shot
by a Vulcan before?

82
00:09:04,503 --> 00:09:05,663
Let's have another game, okay?

83
00:09:06,005 --> 00:09:08,371
We haven't done any work yet today.

84
00:09:09,475 --> 00:09:11,773
Every game has its weak point.

85
00:09:12,178 --> 00:09:15,272
Otherwise how could l win at FF8
in under 8 hours?

86
00:09:16,315 --> 00:09:19,409
You're crazy!
Why didn't you upgrade the RPG?

87
00:09:19,719 --> 00:09:21,516
Just 8 hours!

88
00:09:21,721 --> 00:09:24,087
Can you beat it in eight hours?

89
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:28,727
The Command and Conquer ll you ordered
has arrived. Do you want it now?

90
00:09:28,861 --> 00:09:30,192
- Sure. Thank you.
- l'll go get it.

91
00:09:30,663 --> 00:09:32,631
What the hell? Didn't you buy it already?

92
00:09:33,099 --> 00:09:35,033
Never mind, l'll give it to you.

93
00:09:35,334 --> 00:09:36,995
l've already bought it, too.

94
00:09:37,169 --> 00:09:38,830
Why do l need another one?

95
00:09:39,972 --> 00:09:41,132
You really don't understand?

96
00:09:42,975 --> 00:09:44,033
Of course l don't.

97
00:09:45,011 --> 00:09:47,172
Thank you, if we get some new stock,
l'll call you.

98
00:09:47,313 --> 00:09:48,974
- Thanks!
- Goodbye...

99
00:09:50,316 --> 00:09:51,476
Thank you.

100
00:09:53,486 --> 00:09:55,818
There new games
aren't any challenge for me.

101
00:09:56,589 --> 00:09:58,682
lsn't our business challenging enough?

102
00:09:58,891 --> 00:10:00,950
The company hasn't made any profit yet,
you know?

103
00:10:01,293 --> 00:10:03,523
We will by next month.

104
00:10:04,163 --> 00:10:08,099
l told the boss of the United Company
that he has a virus in his computers.

105
00:10:08,234 --> 00:10:10,566
And to renew all his 3-D video cards.

106
00:10:12,638 --> 00:10:15,129
What's the relationship
between a virus and 3-D video cards?

107
00:10:15,608 --> 00:10:18,543
No direct relationship,
but we have plenty of stock, that's all.

108
00:10:19,078 --> 00:10:20,773
Remember what you promised Jennifer?

109
00:10:20,946 --> 00:10:22,345
Buy some more stock, okay?

110
00:10:22,481 --> 00:10:24,472
Sure, sure...

111
00:10:24,684 --> 00:10:26,276
You still think l was wrong?

112
00:10:26,752 --> 00:10:29,812
Forget it. That fat bastard is rich.

113
00:10:30,022 --> 00:10:32,991
He can use that computer
to check stock prices.

114
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:36,322
He'll find it looks so sharp and clear.

115
00:10:36,462 --> 00:10:39,488
13,000 points will leap out
from the screen at him!

116
00:10:41,567 --> 00:10:42,397
Fai?

117
00:10:43,335 --> 00:10:45,030
'Cool Guy' Fai!

118
00:10:46,872 --> 00:10:48,965
Stop! Why are you running away?

119
00:10:49,742 --> 00:10:51,266
- Do you have any stock?
- What stock?

120
00:10:52,578 --> 00:10:53,977
Keep it down or you'll get me in trouble!

121
00:10:57,316 --> 00:10:59,910
What 'shit'?
This is for the love of my life.

122
00:11:01,153 --> 00:11:02,211
Do you have any stock?

123
00:11:02,722 --> 00:11:04,713
Next time! You're the next on my list...

124
00:11:05,224 --> 00:11:07,624
You think l'm an idiot?
That list is endless!

125
00:11:08,494 --> 00:11:11,793
Save your breath. l'll pay
ten thousand more than any price offered.

126
00:11:16,001 --> 00:11:17,127
For real?

127
00:11:17,503 --> 00:11:18,561
You got one now?

128
00:11:18,704 --> 00:11:20,501
Cash on delivery.

129
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:22,607
Wait here!

130
00:11:23,175 --> 00:11:25,575
You promised to give it to me!

131
00:11:25,711 --> 00:11:28,646
- How can you sell it to him?
- Ten thousand!

132
00:11:28,981 --> 00:11:30,312
You're a sucker when it comes to women.

133
00:11:30,449 --> 00:11:31,780
Can't you show some class?

134
00:11:32,351 --> 00:11:34,785
Come on! l didn't do anything.

135
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:37,150
That's my point exactly!

136
00:11:37,857 --> 00:11:40,052
l've never seen you
seriously chase a girl.

137
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,660
Tell me, which one do you like?

138
00:11:42,895 --> 00:11:43,953
l'll hook you up.

139
00:11:44,463 --> 00:11:45,521
You really don't understand me.

140
00:11:45,664 --> 00:11:47,996
Each girl has her own special charm.

141
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,292
You're one sick dude!

142
00:11:49,468 --> 00:11:52,835
Don't give me that 'true romance' crap!

143
00:11:53,038 --> 00:11:55,268
- l'm not impressed.
- So l'm a romantic...

144
00:11:55,407 --> 00:11:56,601
For Christ's sake!

145
00:11:56,942 --> 00:11:58,068
Here comes your Juliet, Romeo!

146
00:11:59,345 --> 00:12:00,141
Hi! Why so early?

147
00:12:00,446 --> 00:12:01,310
You said you'd come at this time.

148
00:12:01,447 --> 00:12:02,846
So l brought you this.

149
00:12:05,017 --> 00:12:06,644
Are you going to cook?

150
00:12:06,886 --> 00:12:09,446
No, l just prepared some hot pot.

151
00:12:12,725 --> 00:12:13,885
What's that?

152
00:12:15,094 --> 00:12:17,187
This is your dream toy!

153
00:12:18,898 --> 00:12:21,264
A robot dog?

154
00:12:22,568 --> 00:12:24,195
lt's so cute! Where did you buy it?

155
00:12:24,336 --> 00:12:25,735
lsn't it? See?

156
00:12:26,305 --> 00:12:27,795
More money from your honey.

157
00:12:28,407 --> 00:12:30,898
- How much was it?
- Sixty thousand dollars.

158
00:12:31,744 --> 00:12:34,474
Hey, you haven't cleared
your credit card bill yet!

159
00:12:36,315 --> 00:12:38,545
Don't spoil the mood, okay?

160
00:13:15,721 --> 00:13:18,121
- Don't move!
- Greg!

161
00:13:18,524 --> 00:13:20,014
What are you two playing at?

162
00:13:22,895 --> 00:13:24,760
Try putting this cream on it.

163
00:13:25,130 --> 00:13:26,461
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

164
00:13:26,799 --> 00:13:28,198
l'll be in to the kitchen.

165
00:13:30,135 --> 00:13:31,159
Who is she?

166
00:13:31,637 --> 00:13:33,298
Janet, my little sister.

167
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,337
She wasn't that pretty before.

168
00:13:37,209 --> 00:13:39,803
l suspect she had
plastic surgery in Canada...

169
00:13:42,481 --> 00:13:44,915
- Happy now, eh?
- Right!

170
00:13:47,253 --> 00:13:48,311
What a waste of money.

171
00:13:50,356 --> 00:13:51,755
You shouldn't say
such things about your sister.

172
00:13:51,891 --> 00:13:53,119
My sister isn't the problem.

173
00:13:53,259 --> 00:13:56,524
Even a rich guy shouldn't
waste his money on women.

174
00:13:58,664 --> 00:13:59,858
So, are you broke now?

175
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:02,130
That has nothing to do with her.

176
00:14:02,935 --> 00:14:04,425
l admit that l'm a big spender.

177
00:14:05,137 --> 00:14:06,695
But, don't blame Janet for that.

178
00:14:07,139 --> 00:14:08,538
l can tell.

179
00:14:09,375 --> 00:14:10,842
Look at that new TV set!

180
00:14:12,678 --> 00:14:15,511
And the sound system.
You know how much it cost?

181
00:14:15,915 --> 00:14:17,143
You bastard!

182
00:14:18,384 --> 00:14:19,749
You were so happy at the time!

183
00:14:19,885 --> 00:14:22,149
Of course! You gave me the old one...

184
00:14:30,262 --> 00:14:31,661
Take it.

185
00:14:35,067 --> 00:14:36,295
Thank you.

186
00:14:37,002 --> 00:14:37,969
l'm really touched.

187
00:14:38,270 --> 00:14:40,238
l'll smack you in the mouth
if you try and kiss me again!

188
00:14:40,372 --> 00:14:41,669
Let me put some cream on for you.

189
00:14:48,013 --> 00:14:50,345
Have the vegetables drowned yet?

190
00:14:50,482 --> 00:14:51,710
What?

191
00:14:51,917 --> 00:14:54,886
You've been washing them for hours!

192
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:57,318
l'm not used to doing this kind of work.

193
00:14:58,023 --> 00:15:02,187
Well, you did a good job anyway.

194
00:15:02,328 --> 00:15:03,818
Not a worm to be found.

195
00:15:05,764 --> 00:15:07,527
- Let me tell you something...
- What is it?

196
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:10,191
No more worries.

197
00:15:10,703 --> 00:15:11,931
Why?

198
00:15:14,173 --> 00:15:17,939
My brother gave me money.

199
00:15:18,210 --> 00:15:20,075
What exactly does Greg do in the USA?

200
00:15:20,446 --> 00:15:22,539
He kills bugs, computer bugs.

201
00:15:23,182 --> 00:15:24,706
Can you make a lot of money from that?

202
00:15:25,084 --> 00:15:28,110
l don't know,
but my company is still running

203
00:15:28,253 --> 00:15:29,982
even though it's lost money for years.

204
00:15:35,394 --> 00:15:36,588
- Hey!
- What's the matter?

205
00:15:36,729 --> 00:15:38,629
You haven't touched
this savings box for ages.

206
00:15:38,764 --> 00:15:39,992
l put all the money into it.

207
00:15:40,132 --> 00:15:42,623
- Give me some coins.
- You've already got some.

208
00:15:42,768 --> 00:15:44,326
These are mine, how about yours?

209
00:15:46,572 --> 00:15:49,006
lt's useless to save money like this!
Come on, l'll give it all to you.

210
00:15:49,141 --> 00:15:50,904
lt's better than saving nothing at all.

211
00:15:51,877 --> 00:15:54,437
Maybe you'll need this
to last the rest of your life.

212
00:15:55,914 --> 00:15:57,779
You can't just count on me.

213
00:15:58,917 --> 00:16:01,545
l'm getting together
with some friends tonight.

214
00:16:01,687 --> 00:16:02,949
Why don't you two come along?

215
00:16:04,089 --> 00:16:05,215
Tonight?

216
00:16:05,491 --> 00:16:07,584
What? Scared she might scold you?

217
00:16:08,927 --> 00:16:10,326
No, she wouldn't do that.

218
00:16:10,496 --> 00:16:11,520
That's settled, then.

219
00:16:13,766 --> 00:16:15,165
Ask her to come too.

220
00:16:17,236 --> 00:16:18,260
She can come along?

221
00:16:18,404 --> 00:16:21,339
What kind of place
do you think we're going to?

222
00:16:22,141 --> 00:16:24,507
No, l mean, l don't know...

223
00:16:29,915 --> 00:16:31,644
Major, Colonel wants to see you

224
00:16:33,185 --> 00:16:34,948
You go through the whole list again,
anything that...

225
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:38,419
Yeah, yeah, yeah... anything
that says install, you just circle, OK?

226
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:41,352
l don't know who did this.
All this is wrong, this is wrong.

227
00:16:48,734 --> 00:16:49,792
Sorry!

228
00:16:51,070 --> 00:16:54,039
At ease, Major. So, you want some coffee?

229
00:16:54,673 --> 00:16:56,004
No sir, thank you sir.

230
00:16:56,141 --> 00:16:59,201
So... you are going to be here
working with us for a while.

231
00:17:00,279 --> 00:17:03,715
- l'm transferred, sir?
- Welcome to lnformation Warfare Unit.

232
00:17:04,783 --> 00:17:05,681
Sorry!

233
00:17:06,118 --> 00:17:08,348
Basically here we deal with
computer warfare.

234
00:17:08,487 --> 00:17:10,079
This is Sharon, my assistant.

235
00:17:10,989 --> 00:17:13,583
Sir, l'm not very good at computers.

236
00:17:13,759 --> 00:17:15,021
l know, l know, don't worry.

237
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,889
But you are very good
at catching spies, right?

238
00:17:19,698 --> 00:17:21,461
Sharon, l think, you carry on.

239
00:17:23,068 --> 00:17:24,626
We have launched
a preliminary investigation

240
00:17:24,770 --> 00:17:25,964
into last week's mid-air explosion.

241
00:17:26,105 --> 00:17:27,538
The air force claim that
it was not an accident.

242
00:17:28,941 --> 00:17:30,602
You mean the private plane?

243
00:17:32,244 --> 00:17:35,111
lt belongs to a
well-established company called TDX.

244
00:17:35,314 --> 00:17:36,975
TDX is involved
in several major projects.

245
00:17:37,316 --> 00:17:39,580
With their most famous being
a computer protection system.

246
00:17:40,285 --> 00:17:41,252
Among the passengers killed,

247
00:17:41,386 --> 00:17:44,253
was their president
and a department head.

248
00:17:45,557 --> 00:17:46,717
Who would want to kill them?

249
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:49,752
The US government suspects
that this is a spy scandal.

250
00:17:49,895 --> 00:17:51,954
Someone stole something from the TDX.

251
00:17:52,097 --> 00:17:55,123
lt's a program designed for the US Army.

252
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,665
They are investigating the matter.

253
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:00,435
Who did it?

254
00:18:01,039 --> 00:18:02,529
They are not sure.

255
00:18:02,808 --> 00:18:05,242
But they do have a suspect : Greg Li.

256
00:18:05,911 --> 00:18:07,378
He's gone to Hong Kong.

257
00:18:07,513 --> 00:18:10,277
The US government said
they plan to bring him back.

258
00:18:13,285 --> 00:18:14,217
So, what do you want me to do?

259
00:18:14,353 --> 00:18:16,719
Ah, well, we also need
to conduct our own investigation.

